# Bookly

Bookly is a RESTful API for a book review web service, built with FastAPI, SQLModel, and PostgreSQL. It supports user authentication, book management, and review functionality, with JWT-based authentication and role-based access control.

## Features

- User registration, login, and email verification
- JWT authentication (access and refresh tokens)
- Role-based access control (admin, user)
- CRUD operations for books
- Users can submit and manage reviews for books
- Email notifications (FastAPI-Mail, Celery)
- Asynchronous database operations with SQLModel and SQLAlchemy
- Alembic migrations for database schema management

## Project Structure

